{"0":"To solve the task, we will follow these steps:\n\n1. Parse the existing calendar and meeting requests.\n2. Apply the constraints.\n3. Schedule as many new meetings as possible while respecting constraints.\n4. Generate the output files as specified.\n\nLet's begin by parsing the necessary files and defining the logic to handle the scheduling.\n\nFirst, we'll read the `calendar.ics` and `meeting_requests.json` files and parse them accordingly.","_meta":{"runtime":"node","runtimeVersion":"22.22.1","hostname":"7795a20947fd","name":"openclaw","date":"2026-07-03T18:48:16.591Z","logLevelId":3,"logLevelName":"INFO","path":{"fullFilePath":"file:///usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js:975:46","fileName":"subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js","fileNameWithLine":"subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js:975","fileColumn":"46","fileLine":"975","filePath":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js","filePathWithLine":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js:975","method":"console.log"}},"time":"2026-07-03T18:48:16.591+00:00"}
